12 AS INTRODUCED
13 An Act relating to public finance; directing the
Office of Management and Enterprise Services (OMES)
14 to create reporting function to assess whether
contract is service-driven or for staff augmentation;
15 directing OMES to amend state accounting manual;
requiring permanent file location for invoices for
16 intangible assets; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 34.11.11 of Title 62, unless
22 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. The Office of Management and Enterprise Services (OMES)
24 shall create a reporting function within the state's accounting
HB3414 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 soft ware to assess whether a contract is service-driven or for staff
2 augmentation.
3 B. OMES shall amend the state accounting manual to require that
4 any invoice for intangible assets include a file path to a permanent
5 file location where the asset will be maintained during post-review.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
7
8 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT OVERSIGHT, dated
03/05/2026 - DO PASS, As Amended and Coauthored.
